The '''Trition Trade Route''' was a commercial [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperlane]] located in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] at the edge of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. A continuation of the [[Rimma Trade Route/Legends|Rimma Trade Route]]&mdash;a major hyperlane that connected the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]] to the Outer Rim&mdash;the Trition Trade Route commenced at the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Karideph]] in the [[Minos Cluster/Legends|Minos Cluster]], extending into the remote [[Kathol sector/Legends|Kathol sector]] before eventually terminating at [[Gandle Ott]]. The Trition Trade Route linked several important worlds in the [[Sector/Legends|sectors]] together, and placement on the Trition aided each planet's development and economic growth by giving them easy access to outside [[Merchant/Legends|trade]].

==Description==
The Trition Trade Route was a continuation of the [[Rimma Trade Route/Legends|Rimma Trade Route]], a major commercial [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperlane]] that connected the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]] to the [[Minos Cluster/Legends|Minos Cluster]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. The Trition commenced in the Minos Cluster from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Karideph]], before stopping at [[Pergitor]].<ref name="LOTE" /> The Trition then passed out of the Minos Cluster, and headed deep into the [[Kathol sector/Legends|Kathol sector]] on the edge of known space. The Trition included the Kathol [[Sector/Legends|sector]] [[Capital/Legends|capital]], [[Kal'Shebbol/Legends|Kal'Shebbol]], the worlds of [[Torize]], [[Kolatill]], and [[Charis]], and terminated at the planet [[Gandle Ott]] in the [[Ott system]]. The majority of planets on the Trition were noted for having large industrial and manufacturing bases&mdash;large, at least, by the standards of planets within the Outer Rim Territories and beyond.<ref name="TDC" />

==History==
The Trition Trade Route was established at some point after [[592 BBY]]. Before that [[Standard year/Legends|year]], the Kathol sector was largely unexplored and unsettled. Gandle Ott was the first planet to be colonized in the entire sector, and was settled around 592 BBY. The majority of the planets that made up the Trition were in the Kathol sector, and were colonized later than Gandle Ott. Around [[392 BBY/Legends|392 BBY]], the planet Kal'Shebbol was settled by escaped [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]]. The planet was chosen due to its relative isolation, but it also because of its position on a trade route to Gandle Ott. By [[8 ABY/Legends|8 ABY]], the Trition Trade Route was a vital link in the Kathol sector economy, linking the isolated settlements to the Minos Cluster, and many of the sector's most important and successful worlds were located on its length. Gandle Ott, the terminus for the Route, was also considered the last major planet in the sector before entering the "wilderness," of the Kathol sector, demonstrating that a position of the Trition affected a planet's economy and development substantially by offering access to outside [[Merchant/Legends|trade]].<ref name="TDC" />

==Locations==
===Karideph===
{{Main|Karideph}}
