[[Homeworld/Legends|Homeworld]] of the [[Insectoid/Legends|insectoid]] [[Kari]], '''Karideph''' was located at the junction of the Rimma and Trition Trade Routes in the Minos Cluster. Heavily overpopulated, the planet's primary industry was [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]] production, with all available landmass devoted to [[Farm/Legends|agriculture]]. Despite this, the Kari required constant imports of food, and exported small appliances and machinery. Under the rule of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], Karideph was forbidden from developing or acquiring space flight technology as Imperial authorities feared that, if the Kari ever left their homeworld, their prodigious [[Reproduction/Legends|breeding rate]] would see them overrun [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].<ref name="GG6">''[[Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters]]''</ref>

===Pergitor===
{{Main|Pergitor}}
Located in the Minos Cluster, '''Pergitor''' was a [[Mining/Legends|mining]] planet settled by workers from the [[Jesa Corporation]]. Formerly a lush and fertile world, the inhabitants were forced to retreat to sealed settlements when over-mining caused [[Volcano/Legends|volcanic]] eruptions that [[Poison/Legends|poisoned]] the atmosphere and scoured the native ecosystem. A despotic [[theocracy]] governed Pergitor, heavily restricting the [[Standard day/Legends|day]]-to-day life of the population. [[Mineral/Legends|Minerals]] were the world's main exports, while machinery was the major import. An extensive black market thrived on the planet, [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] in luxury goods.<ref name="GG6" />

===Kal'Shebbol===
{{Main|Kal'Shebbol/Legends}}
Sector capital of the Kathol sector, '''Kal'Shebbol''' was founded approximately four centuries prior to the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. As the colony grew, the planet became a major trading post, and was eventually named as the sector capital when the Kathol sector was formally inducted into the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. During the Galactic Civil War, the planet was under the rule of Imperial [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Kentor Sarne]], who later withdrew the sector from the Empire in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] following the [[Death/Legends|death]] of [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. The planet was [[Battle of Kal'Shebbol|liberated]] by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] in 8 ABY.<ref name="TDC" />

===Torize===
{{Main|Torize}}
A volcanic planet in the Kathol sector, '''Torize''' was a major industrial and manufacturing hub. Ringed by [[Space station/Legends|space stations]], the planet suffered an industrial accident that released toxins into the atmosphere in [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]]. The pollutants worsened the already harsh atmosphere, with inhabitants requiring [[Breath mask/Legends|breath masks]] while outside. In 8 ABY, the world underwent an internal power struggle following the breakdown of Imperial authority in the sector.<ref name="O">{{DarkStryder|adventure=Omens|book=The DarkStryder Campaign}}</ref>

===Kolatill===
{{Main|Kolatill}}
Located in the Kathol sector, '''Kolatill'''{{'s}} main industry was the production of [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] vehicles and parts. Placed under martial law in [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] by [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Tetrum]]&mdash;the Imperial administrator of the planet&mdash;all factories and plants were ordered to produce combat [[Speeder/Legends|speeders]] for the ground elements of [[Moff Sarne's forces]]. Following the liberation of Kal'Shebbol in 8 ABY, the population of Kolatill overthrew their governor, although they suffered a reprisal attack when Imperial forces [[Bombing of Domaz|bombed]] their capital city of [[Domaz]].<ref name="O" />

===Charis===
{{Main|Charis}}
The planet '''Charis''', located within the Kathol sector, had industries devoted to manufacturing and information technologies. Originally a world with a population of one billion inhabitants, a [[Charis uprising|civil uprising]] against Imperial forces in 4 ABY [[Subjugation of Charis|resulted]] in the [[Death/Legends|deaths]] of over one hundred fifty million beings and the destruction of several major cities.<ref name="TDC" />

===Gandle Ott===
{{Main|Gandle Ott}}
The end point of the Trition Trade Route, '''Gandle Ott''' was located in the Ott system of the Kathol sector. With several billion citizens and a large industrial base, Gandle Ott was considered to be the last major world of the sector. Nominally allied with the Empire, the local inhabitants did not mind their presence, as they generally left the population alone. However, in 8 ABY, the majority of Imperial forces were pulled out by Moff Sarne as he retreated from the sector following the fall of Kal'Shebbol. Left alone, the planet's remaining authorities were torn between remaining with the Empire, or allying themselves with the New Republic.<ref name="DIRP">{{DarkStryder|adventure=Death Is Remotely Possible|book=The DarkStryder Campaign}}</ref>

